{"name":"Archive.Wiedijk100Theorems.HeronsFormula","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Geometry.Euclidean.Triangle"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Archive/Wiedijk100Theorems/HeronsFormula.lean#L45-L75","name":"Theorems100.heron","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Archive/Wiedijk100Theorems/HeronsFormula.html#Theorems100.heron","doc":"**Heron's formula**: The area of a triangle with side lengths `a`, `b`, and `c` is\n`√(s * (s - a) * (s - b) * (s - c))` where `s = (a + b + c) / 2` is the semiperimeter.\nWe show this by equating this formula to `a * b * sin γ`, where `γ` is the angle opposite\nthe side `c`.\n"}]}